Package org.lightsleep.entity

Annotation classes and interfaces to be used in your entity classes.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Composite
    If an entity class implements this interface, select, insert, update or delete method of Sql class calls postSelect, postInsert, postUpdate or postDelete method of the entity class after the execution of each execute SQL.
    However if update or delete method dose not have entity parameter, dose not call.
    PostLoad
    If an entity class implements this interface, postLoad method of the entity class is executed after load each row.
    PreInsert
    If an entity class implements this interface, insert method of Sql class calls preInsert method of the entity class before executing INSERT SQL.
    In preInsert method, do the implementation of the numbering of the primary key or etc.
    PreStore
    If an entity class implements this interface, preStore method of the entity class is executed before executing INSERT or UPDATE SQL.
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Column
    Indicates the name of column associated with the field.
    If the column name is the same as the field name, you do not need to specify it.
    ColumnProperties
    Indicates an array of ColumnProperty annotations.
    ColumnProperty
    Indicates the column name associated with the field.
    Specifies the field by property.
    ColumnType
    Indicates the type of column associated with the field.
    If the field type and column type are the same type, you do not need to specify it.
    ColumnTypeProperties
    Indicates an array of ColumnTypeProperty annotations.
    ColumnTypeProperty
    Indicates the column type associated with the field.
    Specifies the field by property.
    Insert
    Indicates an expression instead of the field value used in INSERT SQL.
    InsertProperties
    Indicates an array of InsertProperty annotations.
    InsertProperty
    Indicates an expression instead of the field value used in INSERT SQL.
    Key
    Indicates that the column associated with the field is part of the primary key.
    KeyProperties
    Indicates an array of KeyProperty annotations.
    KeyProperty
    Indicates that the column associated with the field is part of the primary key.
    NonColumn
    Indicates that the field not related to any column.
    NonColumnProperties
    Indicates an array of NonColumnProperty annotations.
    NonColumnProperty
    Indicates that the field not related to any column.
    Specifies the field by value.
    NonInsert
    Indicates that the column related the field is not used in INSERT SQL.
    NonInsertProperties
    Indicates an array of NonInsertProperty annotations.
    NonInsertProperty
    Indicates that the column related the field is not used in INSERT SQL.
    Specifies the field by value.
    NonSelect
    Indicates that the column related the field is not used in SELECT SQL.
    NonSelectProperties
    Indicates an array of NonSelectProperty annotations.
    NonSelectProperty
    Indicates that the column related the field is not used in SELECT SQL.
    Specifies the field by value.
    NonUpdate
    Indicates that the column related the field is not used in UPDATE SQL.
    NonUpdateProperties
    Indicates an array of NonUpdateProperty annotations.
    NonUpdateProperty
    Indicates that the column related the field is not used in UPDATE SQL.
    Specifies the field by value.
    Select
    Indicates ta column expression instead of the column name in SELECT SQL.
    SelectProperties
    Indicates an array of SelectProperty annotations.
    SelectProperty
    Indicates ta column expression instead of the column name in SELECT SQL.
    Table
    Indicates the table name associated with the class.
    If the table name is the same as the class name, you do not need to specify this annotation.
    If you specify @Table("super"), the class name of the superclass is the table name.
    Update
    Indicates an expression instead of the field value used in UPDATE SQL.
    UpdateProperties
    Indicates an array of UpdateProperty annotations.
    UpdateProperty
    Indicates an expression instead of the field value used in UPDATE SQL.
